        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 24 at 9:15PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 915 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Genoa, or 11 miles east of Limon, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hugo, Arriba and Genoa.
</description>
        <instruction>Heavy rain is occurring with this storm and may lead to flooding. Do
not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
